 M= \frac{d}{d\theta} e^{A+\theta B} \mid _{\theta = 0} 
A
B
n\times n
\dot x = (A + \theta B)x,\ x(0) = I
x = X(t,\theta) 
M = \frac{dX(1,0)}{d\theta}
\exp(A + \theta B) = \sum_{k \geqslant 0} \frac{(A + \theta B)^k}{k!}  = \sum_{k \geqslant 0} \frac{A^k + k A^{k-1}(\theta B) + \theta^2( \ldots )}{k!} 
\sum_{k \geqslant 0} \frac{k A^{k-1} B + \theta( \ldots)}{k!}
\sum_{k \geqslant 0} \frac{A^{k-1}}{(k-1)!} B = \exp(A)B
